linear perspective is a geometric technique used to produce
an illusion of space </paragraphs><i xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment=""><paragraphs xmlns="http://www.math.cuhk.edu.hk/~pschan/cranach" environment="" chapter_type="" wbtag="paragraphs">inside</paragraphs></i><paragraphs environment="" chapter_type="" wbtag="paragraphs">  the picture plane.</paragraphs><newline environment="" chapter_type=""/><paragraphs environment="" chapter_type="" wbtag="paragraphs">Though there are medieval paintings which utilize various degrees of linear perspective in the pictorial representation of three-dimensional objects,
